{{Quote|These guys have started up a band of mercenaries since they got lost from their detachment. The problem is that they are just too good, and are ruining my company's chance of getting good deals. The less of them there are, the better for us.|A commoner, to a spacer|<ref name="SWG:AC">{{SWGcite|exp=AED|type=herald|A commoner|Talus}}</ref>}}
The '''Lost Aqualish Regiment''', best known as the '''Lost Aqualish''', were a group of [[Aqualish/Legends|Aqualish]] who had settled secretly on [[Talus/Legends|Talus]] where they lived in isolation since centuries.

==History==
{{Quote|You there. Lookin' for a long term job that involves you getting your hands a bit dirty? If so, I know of a place where you can make some money by taking out a group of Aqualishes. They've got all kinds of good weapons on them you probably can use or sell.|A commoner, to a spacer|<ref name="SWG:AC" />}}
The Lost Aqualish were the descendants of an Aqualish war party secretly positioned on Talus during the [[Corellian/Aqualish war|Aqualish–Corellian War]],<ref name="CDHZ" /> a brief and minor border conflict that took place in the [[Trans-Nebular sector/Legends|Trans-Nebular sector]] centuries prior to the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]].<ref name="Goroth" /> These Aqualish troops discovered a [[Lost Aqualish War Party's Cave|cave]] in the wilderness of Talus and took up permanent residence when they realized that it was the perfect staging ground for their raids.<ref name="SWG:LAWPC" /> When the war ended, the Aqualish remained hidden and continued to live in complete isolation during centuries. Highly paranoid, and often described as crazed by those few who knew of their existence, the Lost Aqualish kept their base well hidden fearing that the war could break out any day. Though there were occasional skirmishes between the Lost Aqualish and the [[Human/Legends|Human]] settlers on Talus, their existence was virtually unknown to the rest of the [[Galaxy/Legends|galaxy]].<ref name="CDHZ" />

[[File:Lost_Aqualish_soldiers.jpg|thumb|left|250px|Lost Aqualish soldiers.]]
The Lost Aqualish had cut themselves off from all outside communication during centuries. Due to their state of isolation, they had no knowledge of the fall of the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Old Republic]] or the Galactic Civil War between the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]] and the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]].<ref name="CDHZ" />

After the [[Battle of Yavin/Legends|Battle of Yavin]], several Lost Aqualish warriors decided to work as [[Mercenary/Legends|mercenaries]] on Talus, seriously competing with local mercenaries.<ref name="SWG:AC" /> In [[1 ABY/Legends|1 ABY]],<ref name="SWG_timeline">{{SWG_timeline}}</ref> a mercenary in [[Nashal]] requested a spacer to attack the Lost Aqualish cave and eliminate as much Aqualish as possible.<ref name="SWG:AC" />

Around the same time, several Lost Aqualish outriders were recruited by the [[Followers of Baba]] to act as [[Scout/Legends|scouts]] and [[Sniper/Legends|snipers]].<ref name="LAO">{{SWGTCG|set=Threat of the Conqueror|cardname=Lost Aqualish Outrider}}</ref>

